<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-27T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-27T21:00:00-05:00" n="725" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d725">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00/313: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-27T21:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            27, 1919, 9 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received September 29, 10.10 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>On account of the uncertainty of political conditions inauguration of
                                Leguia as Constitutional President which was to have taken place 28
                                postponed until October 3.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>